article.headline: Wagner 80, St. Francis, NY 78
article.story: NEW YORK -- Llew Radford scored 23 points, including the go-ahead layup with 39 seconds to play, and had 14 rebounds as Wagner beat St. Francis, N.Y. 80-78 on Saturday night. Joey Mundweiler scored eight of his 17 points in a 51-second span late in the game for the Seahawks (8-4, 1-1 Northeast Conference). Mundweiler's fourth 3-pointer of the game gave Wagner a 77-76 lead with 1:40 to go. John Gooden made two free throws 31 seconds later to give the visiting Terriers (3-10, 1-2) a 78-77 lead. After Radford gave Wagner the lead, St. Francis turned the ball over and Chris Martin made one free throw for an 80-78 lead with 27 seconds left. The Terriers got off three shots in the final 11 seconds, 3-point attempts by Stefan Perunicic and Ricky Cadell and one down low by Gooden. Gooden had 19 points for the Terriers while Perunicic and Cadell added 14 each.
